      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMART MISSION (6) has a win around this circuit and will be rock-hard fit for this contest. Reunites with winning hoop Cormack and should be right there when at the business end. ELLIS BEACH (3) was a touch plain at the latest effort but the two wins prior were good enough for a race of this calibre. Can bounce right back. The well-related SHE'S A BEAUTY (5) (half to 2xG2 winner and 3xG1 placed Barb Raider) has been a model of consistency of late and it's hard to knock mares in form. Include with Wiggins on board. TALONS (4) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and may trouble the judge with any luck in running. MORDECAI (7) rounds out the selections in a race with only a handful of chances.",
